<p>Checking units or numbers are two of the easiest and most powerful ways to <term>make sense</term> of something in physics.  When you make sense of something, your objective is evaluate whether or not what physics says about a context aligns with your physical understanding and reasoning about that context.  The steps below will help give you a process to follow for physics sensemaking.</p>

